   <font face="Arial">
    <h1>
     <span style="font-weight: 400">
      <font size="5">
       American Sign Language: "window"
      </font>
     </span>
     <br/>
    </h1>
    <blockquote>
     <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1"/>
     <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
      The sign for "window" shows the opening and closing of a window.
     </p>
     <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1"/>
     <p>
      Use an "up, then down" motion.  The dominant hand (that's means
  the "right hand" for six out of seven people) moves. The base hand
  ("left-hand") stays put.
      <br/>
      <br/>
      WINDOW:
     </p>
     <p>
      <img border="0" src="/images/window.gif" style="max-width: 100%; height: auto" width="480"/>
     </p>
     <p>
      <img border="0" height="240" src="/images/window1.jpg" width="274"/>
      <img border="0" height="240" src="/images/window2.jpg" width="274"/>
      <img border="0" height="240" src="/images/window3.jpg" width="274"/>
      <img border="0" height="240" src="/images/window4.jpg" width="274"/>
      <img border="0" height="240" src="/images/window5.jpg" width="274"/>
      <br/>
      <br/>
      <a href="/images/windowanimation.gif">
       animation
      </a>
     </p>
     <hr color="#800080"/>
     <p>
      "Open-window" uses a single motion.
      <br/>
      <br/>
      OPEN-WINDOW:
      <br/>
      <br/>
      <img border="0" src="/images/window-open-2.gif" style="max-width: 100%; height: auto" width="480"/>
     </p>
     <p>
      <img border="0" height="240" src="/images/window-openwindow1.jpg" width="352"/>
      <img border="0" height="240" src="/images/window-openwindow2.jpg" width="352"/>
      <img border="0" height="240" src="/images/window-openwindow3.jpg" width="352"/>
      <br/>
      <a href="/images/window-openwindowanimation.gif">
       animation
      </a>
     </p>
     <hr color="#800080"/>
     <p>
      <br/>
      To indicate a closed window, start with the window open, then close it.  Use a single quick
  motion.  The right hand is doing all the moving.
      <br/>
      <br/>
      CLOSE-WINDOW:
      <br/>
      <img border="0" src="/images/window-close.gif" style="max-width: 100%; height: auto" width="480"/>
     </p>
     <p>
      <img border="0" height="240" src="/images/window-closewindow1.jpg" width="352"/>
      <img border="0" height="240" src="/images/window-closewindow2.jpg" width="352"/>
      <img border="0" height="240" src="/images/window-closewindow3.jpg" width="352"/>
     </p>
     <p>
      <a href="/images/window-closewindowanimation.gif">
       animation
      </a>
     </p>
